                                                                                Department of the Navy
                                                                         FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                       Operation and Maintenance, Marine Corps
                                                                           Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                                                             Activity Group: Base Support
                                                                  Detail by Subactivity Group: Base Operating Support

                                                                                                                                                     ($ in Thousands)

C. Reconciliation of Increases and Decreases                                                                                                     Amount         Total
  a)Program Decrease in FY 2027                                                                                                                               -62,482
      i)Civilian Personnel. Increase in civilian personnel full-time equivalents and associated funding to support the Commandant's               11,839
         Force Design Reinvestment by addressing known deficiencies in base and station operations across the Marine Corps.
         Provides critical relief to emergency services-police, fire, and first responders-to meet directed staffing levels and safeguard
         life and property aboard Marine Corps installations. Funding adjustment corrects underpricing of civilian personnel across the
         portfolio, aligning resources with validated requirements and program specific cost factors. (Baseline: $906,751; +25 civilian
         FTE)
      ii)Civilian Personnel. Decreases Indirect-Hire Foreign National (IHFN) full-time equivalents and funding to align with the                     -61
         Defense Policy Review Initiative (DPRI) program of record and force realignments across INDOPACOM. This reduction
         supports phased movement of capabilities and infrastructure development timelines. (Baseline: $27,229; -5 civilian FTE)
      iii)Other Base Services. Facilities Asset Management decrease reflects a reduction in fewer master plans, real estate maps and               -127
         boundary surveys. (Baseline: $1,170,385)
      iv)Administration. Financial Personnel Resource Management decrease reflects a reduction in fiscal advisory services, customer               -856
         support and internal evaluation and analysis for Marine Corps Bases and Installations. (Baseline: $369,627)
      v)Retail Supply Operations. Procurement and Supply Operations decrease reflects the elimination of DPRI contract support for                -2,615
         Marine Corps Base (MCB) Camp Blaz. (Baseline: $126,799)
      vi)Civilian Personnel. Reduces funding to align with the adjusted Federal Employees Retirement System (FERS) contribution                   -3,424
         rates. These adjustments incorporate updated actuarial assumptions, workforce demographic shifts, and revised projections of
         retirement liabilities. (Baseline: $906,751)
      vii)Other Morale, Welfare, and Recreation. Marine Corps Force Resiliency decrease reflects efficiencies found in the Other                  -7,050
         Morale, Welfare, and Recreation program. (Baseline: $249,539)
      viii)Administration. Installations Command and Staff Support decrease is attributed to reduced requirements for Naval Facilities           -10,111
         Engineering Systems Command Pacific (NAVFAC PAC) services and contract support at Marine Corps Base Camp Blaz.
         (Baseline: $369,627)
      ix)Operations of Utilities. Utilities decrease reflects reduction in utilities for installations, to include: electricity, steam, water,   -50,077
         wastewater collection treatment and disposal, hot water, chilled water, pneumatic air, natural gas, and utility supplied fuels.
         (Baseline: $353,557)
FY 2027 Budget Request                                                                                                                                      3,175,027




