II. Force Structure Summary:
Marine Corps schools and training centers are managed by TECOM, Quantico, Virginia. The TECOM HQ encompasses the traditional functions of a three-star command, as well
as the functions of the service-level proponent for the Commandant's Title X responsibilities to train and educate the force. TECOM is composed of five Major Subordinate
Commands, nine Headquarters Divisions, and special staff.

Marine Air Ground Task Force Training Center (MAGTF-TC)
Education Command/Marine Corps University (EDCOM/MCU)
Training Command (TRNGCMD)
Marine Corps Recruit Depot Parris Island (MCRD PI)
Marine Corps Recruit Depot San Diego (MCRD SD)

