      iv)Mission Support Programs Atlantic: increase is essential for Global Force Projection, underwriting the strategic mobility of         54,994
         our most critical expeditionary forces. It directly pays for the airlift and sealift required to move the II Marine Expeditionary
         Force, Navy Special Operations Forces, and the Navy Expeditionary Combat Force to and from key theaters like Europe,
         Africa, and the Middle East. Simply put, this funding ensures that when a crisis erupts, our rapid response forces have a
         guaranteed ride to the fight. (Baseline: $296,654)
      v)Navy Expeditionary Combat Enterprise: increase reflects a significant and necessary investment for the Navy Expeditionary             44,850
         Combat Enterprise (NECE). This restoration of resources will directly translate into enhanced combat power, allowing the
         Navy to accelerate the modernization of its expeditionary forces and improve readiness to meet the challenges of a complex
         maritime environment. This funding will enable NECE to double down on critical, forward-looking capabilities. It will allow
         us to field more sophisticated unmanned systems, enhance our battlefield communications, better protect the fleet from
         explosive hazards, and ensure our expeditionary combat forces are equipped and trained to win in a contested fight. This is a
         direct investment in the Sailors who operate at the tip of the spear, ensuring they have the tools and training required to
         execute their demanding global missions. (Baseline: $152,929)
      vi)Naval Forces Europe: increase reflects a major strategic realignment to fund the EUCOM Hybrid Fleet initiative. This critical        35,600
         investment will provide two advanced autonomous maritime systems for experimentation in the European theater. This
         decision directly supports the National Defense Strategy by investing in unmanned capabilities to build capacity and enhance
         maritime patrols in a vital region. By fielding these experimental systems, the Navy will accelerate learning on how to
         integrate autonomous platforms into the fleet, ultimately increasing our surveillance reach, complicating adversary decision-
         making, and providing more options to the combatant commander. This is a clear and deliberate pivot toward the next
         generation of naval warfare. (Baseline: $189,850)
      vii)Navy Special Warfare: increase in projected warfare center support requirements and costs, and adjustments to supported             28,359
         NSW operational capabilities. Fully funding safety-of-life combat support capabilities mitigates the risk of reduced
         equipment reliability and catastrophic failure as age-limited legacy equipment degrades and becomes unsafe and
         unserviceable; and ensures the availability of mission-ready systems required to safely conduct training and contingency
         operations. Program growth also reflects adjustments to projected warfare center support requirements, costs required to
         resource operations for classified Naval Special Warfare (NSW) project A425. Increase appropriately offset by funding
         sourced from the FY26 Mandatory Bill. (Baseline: $129,377)
      viii)Commander Naval Forces Africa: increase provides funding to enhance operational readiness and mission execution for                28,000
         U.S. Naval Forces Africa. These funds are essential for conducting persistent maritime security operations, strengthening
         strategic partnerships, and countering malign influence across the African continent and its vital sea lanes. This investment
         will directly support an increased operational tempo, including multilateral exercises, maritime domain awareness initiatives,
         and security cooperation activities with regional partners. Funding this requirement ensures U.S. Naval forces are
         appropriately resourced to protect U.S. interests, promote regional stability, and remain the security partner of choice in this
         strategically important region. (Baseline: $184,804)

