      ix)Chemical Biological and Radiological Defense (CBRD): increase to procure additional suits to improve Chemical,                          22,405
         Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear (CBRN) defense protective readiness as existing legacy suit inventory is approaching
         end-of-shelf life. Investment provides for the delivery of critical CBRN defense products to deter, prevent, protect against,
         mitigate, respond to and recover from threats. (Baseline: $40,716)
      x)CIVPERS: Increase in civilian personnel Full Time Equivalent (FTE), and funding restores 128 critical civilian FTEs within               21,249
         Combat Support Forces. A post-implementation review determined that the initial reduction, while aligned with broad
         workforce optimization goals, created an unacceptable level of risk in mission-critical areas. This targeted restoration of
         manpower is essential to ensure the effective readiness and mobilization of Navy Expeditionary Combat Command (NECC)
         forces. These FTEs are directly responsible for executing core functions, including logistics management, equipment
         maintenance, expeditionary unit training oversight, and mobilization processing. Restoring these billets is necessary to
         mitigate operational risk and prevent degradation of Reserve force readiness and their ability to deploy in support of Fleet and
         Joint Force requirements. (Baseline: $485,321; +128 civilian FTE)
      xi)Diving and Salvage: increase reflects a critical and deliberate decision to strengthen our nation's premier Diving and Salvage          15,564
         capabilities. This is not a simple top-line addition; it is a strategic realignment of resources, appropriately offset by funds
         sourced from within the Navy's budget, to address urgent readiness and modernization needs. This investment will restore
         critical systems, accelerate advanced experimental diving projects, and ensure the Naval Experimental Diving Unit (NEDU)-
         the DoW's sole facility of its kind-remains the world leader in undersea technology and safety. (Baseline: $30,766)
      xii)CIVPERS: increase in civilian personnel Full Time Equivalent (FTE), and funding. FY26 decrease leveraged a projected                   11,742
         short-term under execution in civilian compensation, driven by hiring lag and natural attrition. (Baseline: $485,321; +64
         civilian FTE)
