         operations and maintenance, software licenses, cyber security activities, and equipment tech refresh in the C7F Area of
         Responsability. (Baseline: $202,094)
      xiv)CIVPERS: Mission Support Program Atlantic/Pacific funding establishes manpower in support of Chief of Naval                            10,371
         Operations (CNO) Learning to Action Board (L2AB) requirements for Surface Readiness Groups, Emergency Area
         Coordinator, U.S. Secretary of the Navy (SECNAV) Special Access Program (SAP), Littoral Combat Ship (LCS) Single
         Crews, Unmanned Surface Vessel (USV) Division 3, and the Board of Inspection and Survey (INSURV). (Baseline:
         $485,321; +59 civilian FTE)
      xv)CIVPERS: Increase in civilian personnel funding based on planned total force management initiatives. This increase will be               9,514
         applied to targeted recruitment, relocation, and retention incentives to secure and maintain a high-quality workforce. This
         strategic investment is essential to attract and retain civilian personnel with the specialized skills required to fill critical and
         hard-to-fill roles. By utilizing these incentives, the Navy can effectively compete with the private sector, mitigate attrition in
         mission-critical areas, and ensure the continuity of expertise necessary for maintaining mission readiness. (Baseline:
         $485,321)

