        Surface Fleet Commanders to execute their ordnance accountability responsibilities. These personnel will conduct critical
        oversight and testing of the fleet's munitions inventory. Their primary function is to ensure the accuracy of Management
        Review Controls, perform inventory validity testing, and oversee remediation and training. This investment is not for a new
        mission, but to provide the workforce required to comply with existing law. It directly ensures the integrity and control of our
        vital ordnance stockpiles, guaranteeing that our warfighters have the weapons they need while providing the rigorous fiscal
        accountability mandated by Congress. (Baseline: $485,321; +6 civilian FTE)
