INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_NAVY_X_217$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$OM_NAVY$$, NULL, NULL, $$Department of the Navy$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, 1C7C
                                                                                                                                                                       (Page 1 of 9)
                                                                             Department of the Navy
                                                                     FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                        Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                                        Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                                                   Activity Group: Combat Operations/Support
                                               Detail by Subactivity Group: Equipment Maintenance and Depot Operations Support


Airborne Mine Countermeasures Equipment (AMCM).

  This program funds the equipment our forces need to detect, classify, and neutralize sea mines, ensuring safe transit for naval and commercial vessels in contested waters. Sea
  mines present a low-cost, high-impact threat that can deny access to critical sea lanes and ports. This funding directly supports the sustainment of our legacy AMCM systems
  and the fielding of modern mine countermeasures on our front-line helicopters.

  Sustaining the Current Capability: This funding provides the essential logistics, maintenance, and engineering support for our existing Airborne Mine Countermeasures
  (AMCM) equipment. It ensures that mission-critical gear is available and reliable for both training and wartime operations. This includes depot-level maintenance, replacement
  of out-of-production parts, and calibration of mission and support equipment, all necessary to keep this vital defensive capability ready for immediate deployment.

  Modernizing for the Future Fight (OAMCM): This funding also supports the continued integration of the new Organic Airborne Mine Countermeasures (OAMCM) systems.
  Deployed on MH-60S helicopters from platforms like the Littoral Combat Ship (LCS), these advanced sensors provide a revolutionary ability to rapidly detect and identify
  mines from a safe distance. This modernization is critical to keeping pace with evolving threats and providing the fleet with the speed and flexibility needed to operate in
  complex littoral environments.

II. Force Structure Summary:

Calibration
The Aviation Metrology and Calibration program maintains aviation core technical capability at 61 Intermediate (I Level) and 20 Depot (D Level) servicing activities worldwide.
The program provides uniform units of measurements necessary to support over 447,000 Aviation Test and Measurement Systems to meet OPNAV and Commander Fleet Forces
Command goals for calibration.

Overhaul Ground Support Equipment
The Aviation Support Equipment program supports approximately 1,992 different end items of support equipment.

