INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_NAVY_X_235$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$OM_NAVY$$, NULL, NULL, $$Department of the Navy$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, 1CCM
                                                                                                                                                                     (Page 1 of 11)
                                                                             Department of the Navy
                                                                     FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                        Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                                        Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                                                   Activity Group: Combat Operations/Support
                                                 Detail by Subactivity Group: Combatant Commander Direct Mission Support
         Fusion Centers: Supports vital Fusion Centers that will coordinate the efforts of whole of government actions with our Allies and Partners.

         INDOPACOM Manpower Increase - Contractor Support: The requirement for increased contractor and civilian manpower supports INDOPACOM ability to Seize
         the Initiative, which encompasses deterrence, decision superiority, and the ability to blind, see, and if necessary kill our theater adversaries. This critical manpower
         requirement is a key priority for USINDOPACOM and is vitally necessary to deter the PRC, and if deterrence is unsuccessful, fight and win.

         Pacific Movement Coordination Center (PMCC): Supports personnel that will develop a regional distribution network essential to see and understand the availability
         of dispersed forces and distribution capabilities operating in a contested environment. It supports regional hubs in Japan, Guam, and Australia that integrate intra-theater
         movements to the point of need.

         USINDOPACOM Campaigning Efforts: USINDOPACOM conducts strategic campaigning to advance regional stability, strengthen alliances, and deter aggression
         across the Indo-Pacific. Through integrated military operations, partnerships, and humanitarian assistance, USINDOPACOM promotes a free and open Indo-Pacific,
         ensuring security and prosperity for over half the world's population. These efforts require sustained investment in advanced capabilities, readiness, and multilateral
         cooperation.

         Joint Interagency Task Force West (JIATF-W): JIATF-W is a U.S. military task force under the United States Indo-Pacific Command (USINDOPACOM) with the
         mission of combating drug-related transnational organized crime in the Indo-Asia-Pacific region. It is composed of personnel from the U.S. military, Department of War
         civilians, contractors, and U.S. and foreign law enforcement agencies. JIATF-W works in cooperation with U.S. interagency and foreign partners to detect, disrupt, and
         dismantle drug-related transnational threats, thereby protecting U.S. security interests.

SEXUAL ASSAULT PREVENTION & RESPONSE (SAPR) / Women's Peace and Security (WPS): The SAPR program is a critical component of USINDOPACOM's
efforts to create a safe and respectful environment for all personnel. Funding supports training, victim support services, and prevention programs aimed at reducing incidents of
sexual assault and ensuring a culture of accountability and respect. Additionally, funding supports initiatives that empower women in conflict-affected areas, enhance their
participation in peace processes, and address gender-based violence. These efforts contribute to building more resilient and inclusive societies.

SERVICE SUPPORT TO PACOM - Special Operation Command - Pacific (SOCPAC): As a sub-unified command, SOCPAC serves as the functional component for all
special operations missions deployed throughout the Indo-Pacific region. The Command coordinates, plans, and directs all special operations in the Pacific theater supporting
USINDOPACOM.

         Campaign Effort in the INDOPACOM (IP) Theater of Operations - Maritime Support Vessel (MSV): Provides INDOPACOM and its components the capability to
         conduct operations at the time of our choosing to influence and shape behavior throughout the theater to reassure allies and partners, keep competitors guessing, and
         achieve Integrated Deterrence.

         SOCPAC Counter Terrorism: Supports actions taken directly against terrorist networks and indirectly to influence and render global and regional environments
         inhospitable to terrorist networks in USINDOPACOM area of responsibility (AOR), which includes areas that support OPE-P in the Philippines.

SERVICE SUPPORT TO PACOM - Global Command & Control Services (GCCS): The United States' armed forces DoW joint command and control (C2) system used to
provide accurate, complete, and timely information for the operational chain of command for U.S. armed forces.

