         necessary logistical, administrative, and operational support-including travel, supplies, training, and equipment-to effectively
         partner with Taiwan and strengthen command and control across all domains. (Baseline: $2,080)
      iii)Increase to sustain USINDOPACOM's direct mission support activities-including headquarters operations, multi-domain                 128,042
         training and experimentation, mission-partner information sharing, logistics command and control, electromagnetic spectrum
         operations, counter-drug missions, and strategic campaigning. This increase is necessary to mitigate the Department's risk
         strategy for FY 2026, which addressed a one-time application of reconciliation funds. The requested funding increase restores
         the program to its historical funding profile, ensuring long-term sustainment. This investment is critical to advancing
         SECNAV priorities for integrated deterrence and warfighting readiness, mitigating long-term operational risk in the Indo-
         Pacific, and ensuring the Command maintains the decisive advantage required to counter the PRC and, if necessary, fight and
         win in a contested theater. (Baseline: $265,626)
      iv)Increase for continued INDOPACOM campaigning focused on Taiwan. This increase directly executes the National Defense                 117,581
         Strategy by bolstering integrated deterrence and enhancing the self-defense capabilities of a critical partner in a contested
         environment. By resourcing the Joint Training Team (JTT), Special Operations Task Force (SOTF), and Joint Task Force
         Micronesia (JTF-M), this investment underwrites essential bilateral engagements that accelerate the development of a
         resilient, all-domain command and control network vital for a coherent combined response. For the Navy, this ensures the
         operational endurance of forward-postured forces and strengthens our ability to maintain sea control and project power,
         directly contributing to a more lethal, interoperable force capable of denying adversary aggression and ensuring a free and
         open Indo-Pacific. (Baseline: $2,080)
      v)Increase in funding establishes critical Counter-Transnational Organized Crime (CTOC) capabilities for Joint Interagency               35,000
         Task Force - West (JIATF-W), directly aligning with Department of War priorities to ensure a free and open Indo-Pacific. By
         targeting illicit trafficking and criminal networks that undermine governance and stability, this initiative actively counters the
         malign influence of state adversaries and enhances maritime domain awareness throughout the USINDOPACOM area of
         responsibility. (Baseline: $0)
      vi)Increase provides essential civilian manpower to bolster INDOPACOM's core headquarters functions and execute highly                   11,349
         specialized missions in priority functional areas. This investment is critical for sharpening the joint force's competitive edge
         and ensuring decision dominance in the Department of War's priority theater. This manpower is fundamental to outpacing our
         strategic competitors. Additional details are held at a higher classification. (Baseline: $45,781; +25 civilian FTE)
      vii)Increase in FTE and funding for the targeted investment in civilian personnel within INDOPACOM. This investment                       7,945
         delivers a critical asymmetric advantage in the priority theater by increasing the analytical, technical, and strategic planning
         capacity of the USINDOPACOM joint force. For the Department of the Navy, this targeted increase in civilian expertise
         directly translates to enhanced maritime domain awareness, more resilient fleet logistics, and superior operational planning
         for sea control and power projection missions. This initiative is essential for outpacing our strategic competitors and directly
         supports the Secretary of War's mandate to build an enduring advantage for a ready, modernized, and lethal force capable of
         dominating the maritime environment. (Baseline: $45,781; +40 civilian FTE)

