      iii)Computer Network Defense(CND): Decrease in funding supporting training and certification requirements to Sailors at Navy          -1,813
         Cyber Defense Operation Command. (Baseline: $43,265)
      iv)Joint Deployable Intelligence Support System (JDISS): The funding decrease fully phases out JDISS program resources                -2,924
         beginning in FY27 and thereafter. This reduction will result in operational degradation within EUCOM's Area of
         Responsibility (AOR), where the Force Disposition Tracker-Maritime (FDT-M) capability provides critical support.
         (Baseline: $2,736)
      v)Other Cyberspace Operations: Decrease due to one-time FY2026 increase to expand infrastructure and facilities and builds            -4,549
         capacity and sustainment in support of Cybercom 2.0. (Baseline: $202,109)
      vi)Implements a strategic reduction of civilian Full-Time Equivalents (FTEs) and funding for Direct and Working Capital Fund         -15,320
         employees in compliance with Executive Order 14210. This workforce optimization is facilitated through voluntary
         separation tools, including the Deferred Resignation Program (DRP), to eliminate redundancies and restore accountability.
         (Baseline: $605,421; -70 civilian FTE)
      vii)The reduction of funding for contracted services is undertaken in direct support of the President's executive order, which       -56,604
         prioritizes cost efficiency, transparency, and the consolidation of services. This measure represents a deliberate workforce
         optimization strategy designed to streamline resources while safeguarding against adverse impacts to modernization
         initiatives and overall mission effectiveness. (Baseline: $605,421)
