                                                                                                                                                                   (Page 1 of 22)
                                                                                Department of the Navy
                                                                       FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                           Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                                           Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                                                           Activity Group: Weapons Support
                                                                Detail by Subactivity Group: Weapons Maintenance
(STRs) annually and providing direct, on-site support to over 130 afloat and ashore commands. This sustainment includes constant cybersecurity updates and information
assurance patching to defend these critical systems against cyber threats.

Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) Services: We fund critical ISR services for Combatant Commands, providing commanders with persistent, multi-
domain intelligence capabilities essential for integrated deterrence and counter-terrorism. In FY27, this will deliver over 10,000 hours of contracted ISR support to meet
the high-demand requirements of commands like INDOPACOM and AFRICOM.

Command, Control & Battlespace Awareness: We sustain the systems that integrate and disseminate intelligence across the fleet. The Geo-Spatial Intelligence (GEOINT)
Unified Naval Streaming System (GUNSS) provides near real-time full-motion video to our ships, while the Undersea Warfare - Decision Support System (USW-
DSS) gives commanders the tools to collaboratively plan and control anti-submarine warfare operations, ensuring a clear and actionable picture of the battlespace.

Unmanned Systems Maintenance — Fielding the Force of the Future
This funds the sustainment of the Navy's rapidly growing and diverse family of unmanned and autonomous systems. These platforms are revolutionizing naval warfare by
extending the reach and sensing of the fleet, providing low-risk options for dangerous missions, and creating the foundation for Manned-Unmanned Teaming (MUM-T).
This funding ensures these high-demand assets are ready to deploy across the air, surface, and subsurface domains.

Unmanned Air Systems (UAS): We sustain a portfolio of UAS that provide capabilities across all operational environments. This includes ensuring the high-altitude MQ-
4C Triton is ready to meet its ISR tasking and maintaining the revolutionary carrier-based MQ-25 Stingray aerial refueler. The goal is to sustain a fleet-wide Mission
Capable (MC) rate of 85% for these critical assets, which act as indispensable force multipliers for the fleet.

Unmanned Undersea & Surface Vehicles (UUV/USV): This funding provides the essential maintenance and engineering for a growing family of unmanned vehicles that
are giving the Navy access to previously unreachable domains. In FY27, we will perform depot-level maintenance on four Knifefish UUVs used for clandestine mine
detection and provide In-Service Engineering Agent (ISEA) support for 15 fielded LCS Mission Packages that rely on unmanned systems. This work is foundational to
expanding our capabilities in seabed warfare, mine countermeasures, and distributed maritime operations.

MANDATORY FUNDING JUSTIFICATION:

The FY 26 spend plan amount for Weapons Maintenance includes $1,303,637 thousand of discretionary and $731,540 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total
of $2,035,177 thousand.




