II. Force Structure Summary:

Weapons & Ordnance Sustainment
This funding ensures the kinetic weapons that arm our ships, submarines, and aircraft are ready for the fight.
  Aviation Weapons Support:
    Missile Maintenance: Sustains 16 air-launched missile systems (e.g., AMRAAM, Sidewinder, HARM) used by 213 Fleet and Training squadrons.
    Ordnance Maintenance: Supports 15 weapon systems, including precision-guided bombs and aircraft gun systems, across 272 Fleet and Training squadrons.
  Subsurface Force:
    MK 48 Heavyweight Torpedoes: Supports the maintenance and readiness of the entire HWT inventory, ensuring our submarine force has its primary offensive weapon
    ready.
    Submarine Combat Systems: Provides essential maintenance and fleet support for the combat systems installed on all operating submarines, including the Los Angeles,
    Seawolf, Ohio, and Virginia classes.
  Surface Force:
    Tomahawk Strike Weapon System: Sustains the Tomahawk capability across a force of 135 firing units (85 surface ships and 50 submarines) and supports the 19
    Intermediate Maintenance Activities (IMAs) worldwide that maintain weapon readiness.
    Surface-Launched Missiles: Maintains the launchers and missile inventories for systems like STANDARD Missile, ESSM, and RAM across the entire surface combatant
    fleet of Cruisers and Destroyers.
    Gun Systems: Supports the CIWS, MK 45, and MK 38 gun systems installed on nearly every surface combatant and amphibious ship in the Navy.
  Direct Fleet Support:
    Weapons Engineering Technical Services (ETS): Provides 46 work-years of embedded subject matter expertise, delivering direct, on-site technical and maintenance support
    at 23 key Navy and Marine Corps installations worldwide.

C4ISR & Mission Planning
This funding sustains the critical "digital backbone" that enables mission planning, situational awareness, and decision superiority for the fleet.
  Mission Planning Systems:
    Navy Mission Planning System (NavMPS): Provides software and hardware support for over 4,000 mission planning laptops and servers used by 43 different
    Type/Model/Series (T/M/S) aircraft.
    Collaborative Mission Planning Continuum (CMPC): Sustains the next-generation mission planning environment, initially supporting 6 T/M/S aircraft and scaling to
    support 28 T/M/S in the future.
    Theater Mission Planning Center (TMPC): Supports 181 TMPC sites, including installations on 11 Carrier Strike Groups and all 133 Tomahawk-capable Firing Units.
  Battlespace Awareness & ISR:
    Geo-Spatial Intelligence (GUNSS): Provides an enterprise-wide license for streaming full-motion video, supporting over 78 ships (CVNs, DDGs, LHDs, etc.) and tactical
    sites, with plans to expand to over 90 platforms.
    INDOPACOM ISR Support: Directly supports integrated deterrence by funding over 300 monthly flight hours for two contractor-owned/contractor-operated ISR aircraft in
    the Philippines.
    AFRICOM ISR Support (ARIES): Provides enterprise-level ISR services to achieve DoW outcomes in the USAFRICOM area of responsibility.

Unmanned Systems

