This funding provides for the maintenance and readiness of the Navy's growing family of unmanned systems, which are extending the reach and sensing of the fleet across all
domains.
  Unmanned Air Systems (UAS):
    MQ-4C Triton: Sustains an inventory growing to 18 air vehicles in FY27, supporting three persistent, OCONUS maritime surveillance orbits from multiple Forward
    Operating Bases.
    MQ-25 Stingray: Supports the stand-up of the first operational squadrons (VUQ-10, 11, 12), with initial CVN deployment planned for FY29. This program will ultimately
    deliver 76 air vehicles to the fleet.
    MQ-9A Reaper: Sustains 20 USMC air vehicles and 16 Ground Control Stations, providing critical ISR-T capabilities in the USINDOPACOM, USCENTCOM, and
    USNORTHCOM areas of responsibility.
    Navy Family of Small UAS (FoSUAS): Sustains a diverse inventory of over 875 tactical UAS providing direct support to Navy Expeditionary forces.
    Tactical UAS ISR Services: Provides over 6,700 hours per month of contractor-owned/contractor-operated ISR imagery from sea and shore to support Fleet, OIR, 5th, and
    6th Fleet operations.
  Unmanned Maritime Systems:
    LCS Mission Modules: Provides engineering and maintenance support for 15 Surface Warfare (SUW) and Mine Countermeasures (MCM) Mission Packages designed for the
    Littoral Combat Ship.
    Knifefish UUV: Sustains the inventory of unmanned undersea vehicles dedicated to the clandestine detection of sea mines.
    MCM Class & Systems: Provides legacy maintenance and depot support for the mine hunting and combat systems aboard our 8 dedicated Mine Countermeasures (MCM)
    class ships.




