      iv)Accounting Systems: Decrease is a result of the ongoing decommissioning of legacy FM Systems: Standard Accounting,              -1,416
         Budgeting and Reporting System (SABRS) and Command Financial Management Systems (CFMS) as a result of finalized
         Navy Migration into Navy ERP and programs closing out expiring year documents in legacy systems. (Baseline: $6,857)
      v)Implements a strategic reduction of civilian Full-Time Equivalents (FTEs) and funding for Direct and Working Capital Fund        -8,045
         employees in compliance with Executive Order 14210. This workforce optimization is facilitated through voluntary
         separation tools, including the Deferred Resignation Program (DRP), to eliminate redundancies and restore accountability.
         (Baseline: $51,968; -18 civilian FTE)
      vi)NGEN - Cloud Services (NMCL): Decrease due to one-time FY2026 increase required to integrate Flank Speed tenant,                -9,532
         Network Transport, and DISA DoW 365 Integrated Phone System (DIPS) service and to add capacity to support audio
         conferencing and off-net dialing using MS Teams to NMCI users. (Baseline: $82,306)
      vii)Electronic Procurement Systems (ePS) & eBusiness Suite Systems: The decrease reflects the accelerated timeline in FY25         -9,803
         and FY26 to deploy a fully functional and auditable Electronic Procurement System (ePS) while phasing out legacy systems,
         including the Standard Procurement System (SPS), NMCI Enterprise Services Tool (NEST), Integrated Technical Item
         Management and Procurement (ITIMP), and Seaport. (Baseline: $29,853)
      viii)Identity, Credential, and Access Management (ICAM) Implementation: DON OCIO support decreases due to the Audit               -12,372
         Relevant System Integration of financial management systems supporting ICAM compliance completion in FY 2027 in
         accordance with the ICAM strategy schedule requirements. (Baseline: $12,372)
      ix)Navy Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP): Decreased support funding for ERP is the result of the completed ERP migration        -15,000
         for the Navy's last three Commands: Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet (PACFLT), United States Fleet Forces Command
         (USFFC), and U.S. Navy Reserve Forces (RESFOR). (Baseline: $694,116)
      x)Strategic Mobile Virtual Network Operators in INDOPACOM: A one-time budgetary reduction was enacted in FY26 to                  -30,000
         specifically fund a Congressional priority: The establishment of Strategic Mobile Virtual Network Operators (MVNOs)
         within the United States Indo-Pacific Command (INDOPACOM) area of responsibility. This reallocation of resources is
         intended to accelerate the development of this key capability in the region. (Baseline: $30,000)
      xi)The reduction of funding for contracted services is undertaken in direct support of the President's executive order, which     -90,976
         prioritizes cost efficiency, transparency, and the consolidation of services. This measure represents a deliberate workforce
         optimization strategy designed to streamline resources while safeguarding against adverse impacts to modernization
         initiatives and overall mission effectiveness. (Baseline: $2,161,697)
